article.headline: Wyoming 81, Indiana St. 51
article.story: LARAMIE, Wyo. -- Desmar Jackson scored 17 points as Wyoming rolled to an 81-51 win over Indiana State on Saturday night. JayDee Luster added a career-high 15 points for the Cowboys (3-5), which snapped a three-game skid, while Amath M?Baye scored 12 and Djibril Thiam and Afam Muojeke each had 10. Dwayne Lathan led the Sycamores (3-5) with 18 and Jake Kelly had 15. Wyoming, which forced 22 turnovers, went up 54-33 on a 3-pointer by Muojeke with 13:43 remaining and the Sycamores never got closer than 15 after that. The final margin was the Cowboys? widest and came on Joe Hudson?s 3-pointer with 29 seconds left. Kelly scored six points in the first 4 1/2 minutes to give Indiana State a 10-4 lead, but Wyoming, led by Thiam and M?Baye, took control over the next 10 minutes to go up 31-17.
